=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect 3-bromo-5-(trifluoromethyl)aniline as 3-bromo-5-(trifluoromethyl)acetanilide (Ac2O or AcCl/base). | Step 2: Do halogen–metal exchange (e.g., n-BuLi, low T; or corresponding Grignard formation) on the protected aryl bromide, then add N-Boc-4-piperidone to form 1-Boc-4-hydroxy-4-(3-acetamido-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)piperidine. | Step 3: Dehydrate the tertiary alcohol to the alkene, giving 1-Boc-4-(3-acetamido-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)-1,2,5,6-tetrahydropyridine. | Step 4: Hydrogenate the C=C to the saturated 4-arylpiperidine, then hydrolyze the acetanilide and remove Boc to obtain 4-(3-amino-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)piperidine. | Step 5: N-Methylate the piperidine nitrogen (e.g., Eschweiler–Clarke or HCHO/NaBH3CN) to furnish the exact target CN1CCC(c2cc(N)cc(C(F)(F)F)c2)CC1.

